    think='Key observations so far:\n1. No new test files were added in the PR d
iff for LoginCubit or MatchingSocketCubit (gh pr diff --name-only showed no test
files).\n2. The existing matching_bloc_test.dart doesn\'t appear to have been up
dated to cover the new swipe animation events.\n3. The PR is implementing UI-bus
iness separation for LoginPage and HomePage.\n\nLet me check a few more things:\
n- Does LoginCubit get disposed properly? It\'s created with `BlocProvider(creat
e: (_) => login.LoginCubit())` in LoginPage, so it should be disposed when the p
age is popped.\n- Are there any issues with MatchingSocketCubit? Let me check th
e socket client implementation to see if there are issues.\n- Let me check the P
R description/checklist to see if the developer reported running tests.\n\nI als
o need to check if there are issues with the MatchingBloc emitting `MatchingSwip
eAnimation` as a state - this is a new state class that extends MatchingState, a
nd it\'s emitted in the swipe drag handlers. But the `MatchingBloc` also emits o
ther states like `MatchingLoadSuccess`, `MatchingSwipeInProgress`, etc.\n\nWait,
looking at the PR diff more carefully:\n- In `matching_bloc.dart`, `_onSwipeDrag
Updated` emits `_animation` which is a `MatchingSwipeAnimation` instance.\n- `_o
nSwipeDragEnded` emits `_animation` (which could be `MatchingSwipeAnimation`).\n
- `_onSwipeAnimationCompleted` emits `_lastListState!` if not null, then adds `S
wipeActionSubmitted`.\n- `_onSwipeResetRequested` emits `_animation`.\n\nBut `Ma
tchingSwipeAnimation` extends `MatchingState`. The UI in `home_page.dart` uses a
separate `BlocBuilder<MatchingBloc, MatchingState>` with `buildWhen: (prev, curr
) => curr is MatchingSwipeAnimation` to read animation state.\n\nHowever, there\
's a critical issue: when `_onSwipeAnimationCompleted` is called, it does:\n```d
art\n_animation = const MatchingSwipeAnimation();\nif (_lastListState != null) {
\n  emit(_lastListState!);\n}\nadd(SwipeActionSubmitted(...));\n```\n\nBut where
is `_lastListState` being set? Looking at the original code, `_lastListState` ex
isted before. Let me check if it\'s being updated properly in the new events.\n\
nActually, looking at the diff for matching_bloc.dart, I see `_lastListState` wa
s already there. But the new swipe events might not update it. Let me check the 
full matching_bloc.dart file in the PR.\n\nAlso, I notice in `_onRecommendations
Requested`:\n```dart\n_animation = const MatchingSwipeAnimation();\nemit(const M
atchingLoadInProgress());\n```\n\nAnd in `_onSwipeActionSubmitted`, the old code
already existed. Let me see if `_lastListState` is set somewhere.\n\nWait, I sho
uld read the full matching_bloc.dart after the PR to understand the state flow b
etter. Let me also check what happens with `_lastListState`.\n\nAnother concern:
In `MatchingSocketCubit`, the `onMatchCreated` callback does:\n```dart\nemit(Mat
chingSocketMatchReceived(summary));\nemit(const MatchingSocketConnected());\n```
\n\nThis follows the pattern of emitting a "transient" state then re-emitting th
e connected state. But per flutter.md:\n> "连接状态不得覆盖消息列表状态" - BLoC 
中 `ImConnected` / `ImDisconnected` 等连接状态不应作为独立 state 类直接 `emit`，
否则 `BlocConsumer` 的 builder 会因无法识别新状态而回退到 `CircularProgressIndic
ator`，导致消息列表瞬间清空。\n\nBut this is a Cubit, not a Bloc for the list st
ate. The `MatchingSocketCubit` has its own state hierarchy. However, the double-
emit pattern might be okay here since it\'s a separate cubit from `MatchingBloc`
. But wait - the `MatchingSocketMatchReceived` is a state that gets emitted, and
then immediately `MatchingSocketConnected` is emitted. This means listeners only
see the final `MatchingSocketConnected` state if they\'re using `BlocBuilder` be
cause the intermediate state gets overridden immediately in the same event loop?
Actually no, in flutter_bloc, states are broadcast to the stream, so both states
would be emitted. But `BlocBuilder` would rebuild twice.\n\nLet me read the full
file for matching_bloc.dart in the PR workspace.',
