ore thing: In `login_page.dart`, the `BlocProvider` is created inside `build`, b
ut `LoginCubit` is not disposed explicitly. However `BlocProvider` handles dispo
sal automatically. Good.\n\nAlso in `home_page.dart`, the `BlocListener<AuthBloc
, AuthState>` listens for auth state changes to call `connect()` on the socket c
ubit. But what if the user logs out? The socket cubit is never disconnected on l
ogout. In the original code, socket was disconnected in `dispose()`. In the new 
code, `MatchingSocketCubit` is a lazy singleton in `app.dart`, so it lives for t
he app's lifetime. Its `disconnect()` is only called in `close()` (when app dies
